    "comment": "Rationale: Fbxo45 is enriched in synaptic fractions. Fbxo45 immunoreactivity colocalizes with a presynaptic marker, VGlut1, and a postsynaptic marker, PSD-95 in both pre- and postsynaptic structures of excitatory hippocampal neurons in culture. Analyses using immunoelectron microscopy revealed expression of Fbxo45 (brain region not specified).\n\n25/4/2017 Pim\n- \"Cytosol\" was infered from the observation that Fbxo45 does not associate with recognizable intracellular structures and the absence of membrane-targeting domains in the Fbxo45 protein.. Experimental description: Fig. 3A/B: immunoblot analysis of Fbxo45 in adult **mice** is shown.\nFig. 3C: \"immunocytochemistry of primary cultured **rat** hippocampal neurons expressing Fbxo45 is shown.\"\nFig. 3D: Immuno-EM on froze brain sections, **mouse** (see below)\n\n25/4/2017 Pim\n- Contacted the authors asking for species of tissue used in Fig 3D. The authors answered:\n\"Dear Dr. Pim van Nierop,\n\nThank you for asking.\nI'm Hirobumi Tada, first author in JBC paper.\nWe used mouse in the EM study.\n\nSincerely yours,\nHirobumi Tada\n\"\n\nSince the highest resolution data is obtianed with *mouse* species. I propose to annotate the mouse protein.",
